<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="permit-v">permit <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /pə'mɪt/    美 /pər'mɪt/  </p>
<p>[正式用语]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>许可；准许</strong></h4>
<p>to allow sth to happen or sb to do sth
反 forbid： </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Mobile phone conversations are not <strong>permitted</strong> anywhere <strong>in</strong> the library.
图书馆内任何地方都禁止使用手机打电话。</p><footer>2013 天津</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>permit sb sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Please permit me a few words. 
请允许我说几句。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>permit sb to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Permit us to question — to doubt — to not be sure.
要允许我们提问——怀疑——不确定。</p><footer>译林新必修③ – 4</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(使) 成为可能：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’ll pick you up at the airport <strong>if time permits</strong>. 
如果时间允许的话，我会去机场接你。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We’ll start tomorrow, <strong>weather permitting</strong> (= if the weather is good enough).
天气允许的话，我们明天出发。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Cash machines <strong>permit you to</strong> withdraw money at any time.
取款机可以让你随时取款。</p></div>

<p>注: permit和allow的用法相似，permit是正式用语；指天气、时间等客观因素允许时，只能用permit。  </p>
<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>I was the first Western TV reporter <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (permit) to film a special unit caring for pandas rescued from starvation in the wild.  （2016 全国）  </li>
<li>The party will be held in the garden, weather <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (permit).   （2012 全国改）  </li>
<li>Passengers are permitted <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (carry) only one piece of hand luggage onto the plane.  （2011 天津改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. permitted  2. permitting  3. to carry  </p></div>